TriceInterpreters generate log lines from the trices and use the trice ID list til.json as look-up table for the received IDs. The TriceInterpreterWithDynamicStrings
filters the next dynamic string from the ignored bytes on reception of an appropriate trigger trice.

div.div: TriceInterpreters deliver lines. Each line is a string slice containing prefix, timestamp, some trice strings and postfix. If a trice sting contains a newline a line break is generated acording to this rules: Remove newline and add postfix and a line slice is complete. If the trice string has some additional characters after the newline, the next line ist started with prefix, newline and '_col:' of the last active 'col:' and same rule again. In that case it is possible lineWriter gets called several times for one singe trice.
